President Joe Biden delivered a commencement speech at the United States Coast Guard Academy in New London, Connecticut. He praised the graduates for their commitment to service and highlighted the importance of the Coast Guard in economic, environmental, and national security. Biden also discussed the challenges the graduates will face in a changing world, including climate change and global threats. He emphasized the need for the Coast Guard to adapt and excel in these areas. The President also touched on issues such as diversity and inclusion in the military, and the role of women in leadership positions. He expressed his optimism about the future and the important role this generation of graduates will play in shaping it.